This Software Requirements Specification (SRS) document outlines the design and functional requirements for Labelketu, a professional boutique e-commerce platform.

Software Requirements Specification (SRS)
Project Name: Labelketu
Owner: Ketu Sharma

Lead Developer: Abhinandan Sharma

Version: 1.0

Date: January 2026

1. Introduction
1.1 Purpose
The purpose of this document is to provide a detailed description of the external and internal requirements for the Labelketu e-commerce platform. It will serve as a blueprint for the development of the system.

1.2 Project Scope
Labelketu is a specialized boutique website designed to provide a seamless shopping experience for customers and a robust management system for the owner. It consists of a customer-facing storefront and a data-driven administrative dashboard.

2. Overall Description
2.1 User Classes and Characteristics
Customer: Browses products, manages profile, places orders, and tracks shipments.

Admin (Ketu Sharma): Manages inventory, views sales analytics, handles order fulfillment, and moderates reviews.

2.2 Operating Environment
Web Server: Python-based (Flask/Django).

Database: PostgreSQL or SQLite for structured data.

Client: Any modern web browser (Chrome, Safari, Firefox).


3. System Features
3.1 User Panel (Customer Facing)
Feature,Description
Authentication,Secure Sign-up and Sign-in functionality using email and password.
Product Wall,A visual catalog of boutique items with high-quality images and descriptions.
Ordering System,"Shopping cart functionality and ""Place Order"" workflow."
Order Tracking,"Real-time status updates (Processing, Shipped, Delivered)."
Returns/Refunds,Interface for users to request returns within a specific timeframe.

3.2 Admin Panel (Management Facing)

Feature,Description
Product Management,"Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) boutique products (title, price, image, stock)."
Data Visualization,"Dashboards showing sales trends, popular products, and revenue metrics."
Order Manipulation,"Ability to update order status, manage returns, and view customer records."
Review Moderation,Manage product ratings and customer feedback to maintain brand quality.

4. Functional Requirements
4.1 Sales & Pricing Logic
The system must calculate total order value including taxes and shipping fees.

The system must allow the admin to set discount codes or promotional prices.

4.2 Data Visualization Requirements
Sales Report: Bar charts or line graphs showing daily/monthly revenue.

Product Performance: Pie charts showing the most sold categories/items.

Rating Analytics: Average star rating per product to identify customer satisfaction levels.

5. Non-Functional Requirements
5.1 Security
Passwords: Must be hashed before being stored in the database.

Access Control: The Admin Panel must be strictly inaccessible to regular users via URL guarding.

5.2 Performance
Product images must be optimized for fast loading (Simple & Accessible).

The website should respond to user queries within 2 seconds.

5.3 Usability
Mobile-responsive design to allow shopping on smartphones.

Intuitive navigation for non-technical users.

6. Project Credits
This website and its underlying architecture are developed and maintained by:

Abhinandan Sharma > Lead Full-Stack Developer

7. Future Scalability
Integration of payment gateways (Stripe/PayPal).

Automated email notifications for order confirmations.

AI-based product recommendations based on user browsing history.
